24h.text:
Seems like there's main two parts:

**How do we make it intuitive for editors**

Displaying parameters in the text [scales badly](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=London&veaction=edit) and scares away editors. My current best idea for solving this is copying [TemplateData's method](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cat?veaction=edit) (click on the infobox template), but have the template call code highlighted (![highlight](https://i.imgur.com/9g2kWcp.png)) in source editor, and make clicking the template in the source code bring up a form to edit the parameters.

A bonus is storing the parameters separately makes it much easier to reuse the structured information.

**What features does it need to be handle the major use cases**

Essential:

* Single layer transclusion
* [Template parameters](https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Templates#Parameters)

Important

* A way to conditionally hide parts of a template when a variable is not present.
 * Possibly via a basic [parser function](https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Extension:ParserFunctions) for IF?
  * Possibly by using the syntax for parameters so it's easy to specify which parts should only be shown if the parameter is included?
* Core [magic words](https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Magic_words)
 * PAGENAME, PARENTS, CHILDREN, DOMAIN, some time/date ones?

Would be good:

* Multi layer transclusion
  * Not certain about this, but not having it probably causes more problems than having it.
* More flexible scripting for complex templates
 * The only really good implementation I know of is [Scribunto](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Lua)
 * MW got by with parser functions for a while. It worked, but it was ugly and terrible. Maybe a with some thought a parser function like solution could be made less bad.
* A wider collection of [magic words](https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Magic_words)

Wishlist:

* Use the structured data stored in templates to improve search
* Allow in-page display of structured data, like [SMW's Inline Queries](https://www.semantic-mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Inline_queries)
